definitions.definition: Mutually destructive ; most often applied to warfare .
examples: Internecine strife in Gaza claimed its most senior victim yesterday.

definitions.definition: Characterized by struggle within a group, usually applied to an ethnic or familial relationship.
examples: The Mongol people were plagued by internecine conflict until Genghis Khan unified them.

main_definition: Mutually destructive ; most often applied to warfare .
secondary_definitions: Characterized by struggle within a group, usually applied to an ethnic or familial relationship.
